---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { site, absoluteUrl } from "../site.config";

/**
 * /privacy — the LEGAL privacy policy (GDPR/CCPA structured), required for
 * AdSense approval. Leads with the client-side moat (your script never leaves
 * your device) then layers the full legal structure: data controller, what is
 * + isn't collected, the on-device storage model, cookies (GA4 + potential
 * AdSense/DART), third parties, rights, retention, contact. All operator
 * values come from site.config.ts.
 */

const updated = "June 17, 2026";

// WebPage JSON-LD (no dedicated Schema.org PrivacyPolicy type) — layered on
// top of the sitewide Organization + WebSite graph + auto-breadcrumb.
const privacySchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "@id": absoluteUrl("/privacy/"),
  name: `Privacy Policy — ${site.name}`,
  url: absoluteUrl("/privacy/"),
  description: `How ${site.name} handles your data: your script stays on your device, analytics are anonymous, and your rights under GDPR and CCPA.`,
  dateModified: "2026-06-17",
  isPartOf: { "@id": `${site.url}/#website` },
  publisher: { "@id": `${site.url}/#organization` },
};
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`${site.name} privacy policy — your script stays in your browser, never uploaded. What little we process, cookies, third parties, and your GDPR/CCPA rights.`}
  path="/privacy/"
  jsonLd={[privacySchema]}
>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] px-6 md:px-12 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg-subtle)] p-5 leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-fg-muted)]">
      <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">The short version:</strong>
      your teleprompter script is stored only in your browser, on your device.
      We never receive, upload, or store it. We can't read what we don't have.
      The only data anyone processes is anonymous, aggregate website analytics.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">1. Who we are</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} (“we”, “us”, “our”) is a free, client-side web application
          operated by {site.author}. We act as the data controller for the
          limited, non-content data described below. For any privacy question or
          request, contact
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">{site.contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">2. Your script never leaves your device</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} is a fully client-side app. The script you paste or type,
          plus your settings (speed, font size, mirror mode, etc.), are stored
          locally in your browser using <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">local storage</strong>,
          a standard on-device mechanism. Your script content:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>is never transmitted to us or to any server;</li>
          <li>is never stored, backed up, or processed on our infrastructure;</li>
          <li>cannot be read by us, because we never receive it;</li>
          <li>stays on your device until you clear it or your browser data.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          There is no server-side account, database, or sync. The entire app is
          static files served from a content-delivery network. You can verify
          this in the
          <a href={site.githubRepo} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">open-source code</a>
          or by watching your browser's Network tab while you use the prompter.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">3. Information we do process</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To run and improve the website, a limited amount of standard,
          non-content data is processed:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Anonymous analytics.</strong>
            We use Google Analytics 4 to count page views and understand broad
            usage (e.g. which pages are popular, rough country, device type).
            This is aggregate and anonymized — it is never linked to your script,
            which we don't have access to.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Server logs.</strong>
            Our hosting/CDN provider (Cloudflare) may automatically log standard
            request metadata such as IP address and user-agent for security and
            abuse-prevention, as is typical for any website.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">4. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} itself does not use cookies to track you. We use your
          browser's local storage only to remember your own script and
          preferences (such as your theme choice) — never for tracking.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">Third-party services we load may set cookies:</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Google Analytics</strong>
            sets cookies to measure aggregate usage. See
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Advertising (if shown).</strong>
            We may display ads served by Google AdSense. Third-party vendors,
            including Google, use cookies (such as the DART cookie) to serve ads
            based on your prior visits to this and other websites. Google's use
            of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to
            you based on your visits. You can opt out of personalized advertising
            via
            <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">Google Ads Settings</a>,
            or opt out of some third-party vendors' cookies at
            <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">aboutads.info/choices</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">5. Third-party services</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We rely on a small set of reputable providers:
          <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Cloudflare</strong>
          (hosting and content delivery),
          <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Google Analytics</strong>
          (anonymous usage measurement), and potentially
          <strong class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Google AdSense</strong>
          (advertising). Each processes data under its own privacy policy. We do
          not sell your personal information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">6. Your rights (GDPR &amp; CCPA)</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Because your script lives only on your device, you already have
          complete control: you can view, edit, or permanently delete it at any
          time, directly in the app. For the limited analytics data processed by
          our providers, and depending on your jurisdiction (e.g. the EU/UK under
          GDPR, or California under the CCPA), you may have the right to access,
          correct, delete, or restrict processing of your personal data, and to
          object to it.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          To exercise any of these rights, email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">{site.contactEmail}</a>.
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data
          protection authority.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">7. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} is a general-audience utility and is not directed at
          children under 13. Since we collect no personal content, none is
          knowingly collected from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">8. International data transfers</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Our providers (Cloudflare, Google) operate globally and may process the
          limited non-content data described above on servers outside your
          country, under their own safeguards and standard contractual clauses.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">9. Data retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Your script stays on your device until you delete it. Aggregate
          analytics are retained by Google Analytics under its standard retention
          settings; CDN security logs are short-lived per Cloudflare's policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">10. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
          reflected by the “Last updated” date above. Continued use of
          {site.name} after a change constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-fg)]">11. Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions about this policy or your data? Email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">{site.contactEmail}</a>
          or open an issue on
          <a href={site.githubRepo} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">GitHub</a>.
          See also our <a href="/terms/" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">Terms of Use</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
